The land cover data above is from here from Copernicus.

I hate almost eveyrthing about this plot but generally it looks like a cline of thinning forest from S-N with some shrubland roughly where Mafalda defined the forest park as. So let’s make sure we have some samples represented by all of these.

Toggling the opacity so the general horrendousness of the colour and annotations doesn’t kill us. But I think let’s pick: 37, 8, 27, 23, 32, 13, 12, 35, 24, 18
